TITLE: NYC Democrats Grant Voting Rights to Nearly 1 Million Noncitizens
SUMMARY: Up to one million noncitizens living in New York City will have access to the ballot box after Mayor Eric Adams (D) on Sunday approved legislation by the city council to automatically become law.

TITLE: Report: Capitol Police Alerted to 'Suspicious Package' near House Office Building
SUMMARY: Discovery of what was described as a "suspicious package" outside the Rayburn House Office Building in Washington, DC, Sunday morning sparked an urgent call out for U.S. Capitol Police.

TITLE: Unaccountable: Joe Biden's First Year Marked by Fleeing News Conferences, Interviews
SUMMARY: President Joe Biden will mark the end of his first 12 months in office with the singular record of holding fewer news conferences than any of his five immediate predecessors at the equivalent point in their tenure.

TITLE: Los Angeles County Experiences Highest Weekly Coronavirus Totals of Pandemic
SUMMARY: Los Angeles County reported its highest weekly total infections from coronavirus of the entire pandemic on Saturday, with over 200,000 cases across the week, as well as a rise in hospitalizations, though severe illness is lower than it was previously.

TITLE: Chicago Mayor Lightfoot: ‘What the Chicago Teachers Union Did Was an Illegal Walkout’
SUMMARY: Chicago Mayor Lori Lightfoot said Sunday on NBC's "Meet the Press" that the Chicago Teachers' Union had their teachers take part in an "illegal walkout" by refusing to show up for in-person learning over fears of coronavirus.

TITLE: Tapper: Confederate Statues in Congress Are 'Tributes to Traitors,' Honors 'Political Violence'
SUMMARY: CNN anchor Jake Tapper said Sunday on his show "State of the Union" that the statues of Confederate leaders in Congress are "tributes to traders" that honor political violence like the events of January 6, 2021.

TITLE: It Worked: Over 100,000 French Protest Vax Pass After Macron Vowed to ‘Piss Off’ Unvaxed
SUMMARY: Over 100,000 took to the streets on Saturday to protest France's impending vaccine pass regime days after President Macron said he wanted to "piss off" the unjabbed.

TITLE: Power Goes Out During South African President Cyril Ramaphosa's Speech at Fundraiser
SUMMARY: The power went out Saturday night as South African President Cyril Ramaphosa addressed a gala fundraising dinner for his ruling party, the African National Congress (ANC), causing embarrassment to the government and forcing his evacuation.

TITLE: Nolte: 'The 355' Is Another Woketard Box Office Flop
SUMMARY: The 355 an action movie that offers five fairly big stars — Jessica Chastain, Lupita Nyong’o, Penélope Cruz, Diane Kruger and Fan Bingbing — and with no serious competition at the box office, it dies a humiliating $4 million death.

TITLE: Delingpole: 'Make the Unvaccinated Pay!' Demands Failed Ex-PM's Sister-in-Law
SUMMARY: "It's time for London's unvaccinated to pay with their freedoms, not ours", said David Cameron's sister-in-law in a hard-hitting editorial for the Evening Standard, a London free-sheet widely used in cat litter trays across the Metropolis.

TITLE: Asa Hutchinson: GOP Needs to 'Not Diminish' January 6, Trump Had 'Responsibility'
SUMMARY: Governor Asa Hutchinson (R-AR) said Sunday on CNN's "State of the Union" that for long-term success, the Republican Party needs to stop diminishing the events of January 6, 2021, and admit former President Donald Trump has "responsibility."

TITLE: Cartel Gunmen, Police Clash in Mexican Border City
SUMMARY: Chaos spread in a Mexican border city as a group of gunmen from the Gulf Cartel clashed with state police forces. Most of the gunmen escaped as authorities managed two arrests. Police also seized two vehicles and weapons.

TITLE: India Blocks Then Restores Foreign Funding for Mother Teresa’s Order
SUMMARY: ROME — The Indian government has restored the Missionaries of Charity to its list of associations approved for receiving foreign funding after suspending the order’s license on Christmas.

TITLE: Paul Finebaum Calls Baker Mayfield 'A Poor Man's Johnny Manziel'
SUMMARY: ESPN college football analyst Paul Finebaum called Cleveland Browns QB Baker Mayfield a "poor man's Johnny Manziel" during a recent interview.

TITLE: Nolte: Fox News Drinks the Trans Kool-Aid
SUMMARY: “‘Jeopardy!’ champ Amy Schneider hits $1 million, becomes first woman to land accolade," screams a fake headline at Fox News.
